  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6845 sitting just below the massive 6850 gamma wall (11.8B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher as they hedge their long gamma exposure. The recent wall break and GEX surge events suggest we've seen significant options flow that's now creating a powerful magnet effect around current levels, with dealers providing liquidity against directional moves. Key resistance at 6850 should cap upside while the 6840 level (4.8B GEX) provides additional selling pressure, and any meaningful dip toward 6796 (GEX flip) would shift the dynamic entirely.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect strong resistance near 6850 with dealers capping rallies and supporting dips around current levels.",
